  "prompt": "How long does it take to get an Australia PR visa in general?",
  "response": "The processing time for an Australian Permanent Residency (PR) visa can vary significantly based on several factors, including the specific visa subclass, the applicant's individual circumstances, the completeness of the application, and the demand and workload at the Department of Home Affairs.\n\nIn general, processing times for PR visa applications can range from several months to a couple of years. Here are some examples of common PR visa subclasses and their typical processing times:\n\n1. **Skilled Independent visa (subclass 189)**: This visa is often processed within 9 to 18 months.\n2. **Skilled Nominated visa (subclass 190)**: The processing time is usually around 9 to 15 months.\n3. **Employer Nomination Scheme visa (subclass 186)**: Processing can take anywhere from 8 to 16 months.\n4. **Regional Sponsored Migration Scheme visa (subclass 187)**: The processing time typically ranges from 12 to 24 months.\n5. **Partner visa (subclass 801)**: It often takes between 12 to 24 months to process.\n\nThese timeframes are indicative and subject to change, depending on various factors like the volume of applications received, changes in immigration policies, and the applicant's ability to provide required documentation promptly.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's advisable to check the official website of the Australian Department of Home Affairs or consult with an immigration agent.",
